## `<file-level: constants and overview>`
<!-- checksum: rust-xattrs-1 -->

### Purpose
Extended-attribute CRUD on the `xattrs` table. xattrs are per-inode (hard links share them). Matches Linux limits: name ≤ 255 bytes, value ≤ 64 KiB.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use bitflags::bitflags;
use rusqlite::{Connection, OptionalExtension, params};

use crate::errors::{Error, Result};

pub const XATTR_NAME_MAX:  usize = 255;
pub const XATTR_VALUE_MAX: usize = 65536;

bitflags! {
    /// Bit-flag analogues of `os.XATTR_CREATE` / `os.XATTR_REPLACE`.
    #[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
    pub struct XattrFlags: u32 {
        const CREATE  = 0x1;
        const REPLACE = 0x2;
    }
}
```

---

## `pub fn validate_name(name: &str, caller_uid: u32) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-xattrs-2 -->

### Purpose
Enforce Linux xattr name rules. Length ≤ 255 bytes, non-empty, no NUL, has a namespace ("." separator). `trusted.*` restricted to root.

### Failure Modes
- Empty / NUL / too-long / no-namespace: `Err(Error::InvalidXattr(...))`.
- `name.starts_with("trusted.")` && `caller_uid != 0`: `Err(Error::PermissionDenied(...))`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn validate_name(name: &str, caller_uid: u32) -> Result<()> {
    if name.is_empty() {
        return Err(Error::InvalidXattr("xattr name must be non-empty".into()));
    }
    if name.contains('\0') {
        return Err(Error::InvalidXattr("xattr name contains NUL".into()));
    }
    if name.len() > XATTR_NAME_MAX {
        return Err(Error::InvalidXattr(
            format!("xattr name exceeds {XATTR_NAME_MAX} bytes: {name:?}")
        ));
    }
    if !name.contains('.') {
        return Err(Error::InvalidXattr(
            format!("xattr name must have a namespace: {name:?}")
        ));
    }
    if name.starts_with("trusted.") && caller_uid != 0 {
        return Err(Error::PermissionDenied(
            "setting trusted.* xattrs requires root".into()
        ));
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

