## `pub fn remove(conn, inode, name) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-xattrs-7 -->

### Failure Modes
- No such row: `Err(Error::NotFound(...))`.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn remove(conn: &Connection, inode: u64, name: &str) -> Result<()> {
    let changed = conn.execute(
        "DELETE FROM xattrs WHERE inode = ?1 AND name = ?2",
        params![inode as i64, name],
    )?;
    if changed == 0 {
        return Err(Error::NotFound(
            format!("xattr {name:?} not set on inode {inode}")
        ));
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

---

## `pub fn has_any(conn, inode) -> Result<bool>`
<!-- checksum: rust-xattrs-8 -->

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn has_any(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<bool> {
    let row: Option<i64> = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT 1 FROM xattrs WHERE inode = ?1 LIMIT 1",
        params![inode as i64],
        |r| r.get(0),
    ).optional()?;
    Ok(row.is_some())
}
```

